race.comment: TAKE ACHANCE ON ME (5) resumed at Newcastle, beaten 2.7L and has been switched north by the Waller yard on a three-week return. The speed-bred mare has metro form good enough for this and quick improvement is likely. ENHANCE (1) resumes and just missed returning from a spell last prep on the Gold Coast Poly. Lines up today for new trainer Stephen McLean and his early NSW provincial form is good enough. A player if he recaptured those efforts. PAPER DOLL (3) resumes and is having her first outing under new trainer Les Kelly. Placed in a recent trial and has a handy 3kg claim. Showed enough last preparation to deserve plenty of consideration. BOOMTIME NOW (2) has also switched stable and won a recent trial over a short sprint. Went well on debut, but he's been off the scene for a long time.
